===Etymology 2===
[[File:Oil painting of a man smoking an opium pipe, Europe Wellcome L0058627.jpg|thumb|A painting of an opium-smoker which used to hang in Ah Sing’s opium den on [[w:Victoria, London|Victoria Street]] in London, England.]]
Origin uncertain, but probably from {{der|en|yue|癮|tr=[[jan5|jan<sup>5</sup>]]||[[craving#Noun|craving]]}} originally in reference to opium addiction, {{m|yue|煙癮}} or {{m|yue|菸癮|tr=[[jin1|jin<sup>1</sup>]]-[[jan5|jan<sup>5</sup>]]}}: {{m|yue|煙}}, {{m|yue|菸|tr=[[jin1|jin<sup>1</sup>]]||[[smoke#Noun|smoke]], ''specifically'' [[opium]]}}. Compare the later ''[[#Etymology 3|yen]]'' (“opium”) and {{m|en|yen-yen}}.<ref>"yen, ''n.''²", in the ''Oxford English Dictionary''. Oxford: Oxford University Press.</ref>
