==Indonesian==
{{wikipedia|lang=id}}
===Etymology===
From the influence of earlier {{der|id|pt|-}} romanizations, of {{der|id|ja|圓|t=[[round#Adjective|round]]; a [[round#Adjective|round]] [[object]]}} as ''ye'' or ''yen'', now {{m|ja|円|tr=en}}, from {{der|en|zh|銀圓|tr=yínyuán|t=round [[silver#Adjective|silver]] object(s), ''especially'' a [[piece of eight]]}}: {{m|zh|銀|t=silver}} + {{m|zh|圓|t=[[circular]], round; [[yuan]], yen, [[dollar]]}}.<ref>{{cite-book|entry=Yen|title={{lang|ja|世界大百科事典}}|trans-title=Sekai dai Hyakka Jiten = [[w:Heibonsha World Encyclopedia|Heibonsha World Encyclopedia]]|location=Tokyo|publisher=Heibonsha|year=2007|volume=III|oclc=693636727}}.</ref> Cognate with {{cog|zh|元|tr=yuán|t=[[monetary unit]], ''especially'' [[RMB]]}} and {{cog|ko|원|t=[[North Korea|North]] or [[South Korea]]n [[won]]}}.
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|id|/jɛn/|/jen/}}
* {{hyphenation|id|yèn}}
===Noun===
{{id-noun|}}
# {{lang|en|yen}}, the [[unit]] of [[Japanese]] currency (symbol: [[¥]]) since 1871, divided into 100 sen.
